original_problem:
Find the least positive four-digit solution to the following system of congruences. \begin{align*}
7x &\equiv 21 \pmod{14} \\
2x+13 &\equiv 16 \pmod{9} \\
-2x+1 &\equiv x \pmod{25} \\
\end{align*}

problem:
Find the smallest positive solution to the following system of congruences:
\begin{align*}
x &\equiv 3 \pmod{4} \\
x &\equiv 5 \pmod{6} \\
\end{align*}

original_solution:
Reducing each number modulo 9 first, we get \begin{align*}
88134 + 88135 + 88136& + 88137 + 88138 + 88139\\
&\equiv 6 + 7 + 8 + 0 + 1 + 2 \\
&\equiv 24 \\
&\equiv \boxed{6} \pmod{9}.
\end{align*}
